{"word":"G907 - βαπτίζω - baptízō - bap-tid'-zo - Baptist","slug":"G907","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">βαπτίζω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>baptízō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>bap-tid'-zo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Baptist"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B2;&#x03B1;&#x03C0;&#x03C4;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B6;&#x03C9; - baptizo&#x0304;</b> - <i>bap-tid'-zo</i><p/>From a derivative of <a href=\"#/G911\">G911</a>; to <i>make whelmed</i> (that is, <i>fully wet</i>); used only (in the New Testament) of ceremonial <i>ablution</i>, especially (technically) of the ordinance of Christian <i>baptism:</i> - baptist, baptize, wash."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G908\">G908</a>, <a href=\"#/G909\">G909</a>, <a href=\"#/G910\">G910</a>, <a href=\"#/G911\">G911</a>"}]}